            "text": "structure of coronavirus genome is properly known . There are four 27 structural proteins: spike (S), envelope (E), membrane (M) and 28 nucleocapsid (N). These proteins beside other helper proteins 29 account for One-third of the genome, the other two-third encodes 30 viral polymerase (RdRp), RNA synthesis materials and ORF1a-31 ORF1b (two types of huge nonstructural proteins) (4). S protein is 32 on the surface of the virus and shape the virus as a crown. S 33 protein`s function is making an interaction between the sensitized 34 cell and the virus then the genome can enter the cell. In 35 cytoplasm, genomic RNA encodes various structural and non-36 structural polypeptide genes. Shape of the virus is reforming along 37 with alterations in S-protein-coding genes. The E and M types 38 function as small transmembrane proteins. Nucleocaspide (N) is 39 used for cloning and generation of recombinant proteins. CoVs 40 extremely recombine which is the outcome of repetitively 41 developing transcription errors and RNA Dependent RNA 42 Polymerase (RdRP) jumps (4, 5). 43 Transmission 44",
