        "FIGREF1": {
            "text": "probable transmission routes, but some cases show other ways of 57 transmission like; fecal-oral transmission, fomite transmission 58 (transfer of a virus via an object), perinatal (intrauterine) 59 transmission. There have been few researches, some of which 60 were negative.All routes are under investigation and some 61 researchers believed that the limited samples affect the negative 62 results(7). 63 No reliable study has been conducted on the survival of the 64 coronaviruses in food to indicate foodborne transmission. some 65 microbicides are effective against coronaviruses; for example 66 Alcohols, Aldehydes, Phenolics(8). 67 Clinical manifestations 68 It is essential to be aware of clinical manifestations of COVID-19, 69 even though the symptoms are nonspecific. Common symptoms 70 are fever, nonproductive cough and myalgia or fatigue, normal or 71 decreased leukocyte counts and radiographic evidence of 72 pneumonia. At first people may complain of diarrhea and nausea. 73 A few days later, they develop fever. Fever is usually detected in 74 patients but it is not the main symptom. Headache, dizziness, abdominal pain, diarrhea, nausea, and vomiting are some of the 76 less common symptoms. ICU care is required for aged patients or 77 patients likely to have comorbidities including hypertension, 78 diabetes, cardiovascular diseases and cerebrovascular disorders. 79 Subsequent problems during hospitalization are mostly acute 80 respiratory syndrome (ARDS), arrhythmia, and shock. According 81 to scientific observations, as the status of patient gets worse, urea 82and creatinine blood levels gradually rised(9, 10).Another common 83 symptom in patients is lymphopenia that possibly is a serious 84 issue during hospitalization so there may be correlation between 85 lymphopenia and severity or mortality of the disease (11). 86Diagnosis 87The CORVID-19 is diagnosed based on asking questions about 88 contacts and travel of the patient during past two weeks and 89 accurate tests like molecular methods, serology and viral culture.",
